headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 28 points, Darius Garland added 24 and the Cleveland Cavaliers improved to 13-1 at home with a 126-114 victory Thursday night over the Denver Nuggets, who wasted a triple-double by Nikola Jokic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 28 as Cavaliers improve to 13-1 at home by beating Jokic and Nuggets 126-114

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 21 points, 10 assists and 10 rebounds and Kyrie Irving added 25 points to lead the Dallas Mavericks to a 137-101 victory over Washington on Thursday night, the Wizards' 16th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's triple-double helps Mavericks send Wizards to 16th straight loss in 137-101 rout

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby scored 15 of his 25 points during a third quarter in which he also blocked consecutive 3-point shots on opposite sides of the floor, helping the New York Knicks pull away to...
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby and Towns help the Knicks blow it open on the way to a 125-101 rout of the Hornets

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 30 points, Jalen Williams had 20 and the Oklahoma City Thunder routed the Toronto Raptors 129-92 on Thursday night for their sixth win in seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 30 as Thunder rout Raptors 129-92 for sixth win seven games

headlines.description: — Marcus Smart scored 18 points — the last two on clinching free throws with 2.9 seconds left — and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Sacramento Kings 115-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marcus Smart scores 18 points, hits clinching free throws in Grizzlies' 115-110 win over Kings

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 29 points in his return from a five-game absence, Herb Jones capped off his first game back from a shoulder injury by blocking Devin Booker's last-second shot, and the New Orleans Pelicans snapped a nine-game losing streak with...
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram scores 29 points and healthier Pelicans top the Suns 126-124 to snap a 9-game skid

events.name: Chicago Bulls at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had a season-high 39 points, Ayo Dosunmu had 27 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds and the Chicago Bulls beat the San Antonio Spurs 139-124 on Thursday night with Victor Wembanyama sidelined with a back injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic, Dosunmu lead Bulls to season-high output in 139-124 win over Spurs with Wembanyama out

events.name: Houston Rockets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jonathan Kuminga scored a career-high 33 points and made two crucial layups over the final 1:04, and the Golden State Warriors snapped a five-game losing streak by beating the Houston Rockets 99-93 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jonathan Kuminga scores career-high 33 points, Warriors beat Rockets 99-93 to snap 5-game skid
